 radius\nagrees with theoretical values from standard models, suggesting the presence of\na heavy element core with a mass of ~10 M_earth. The discovery of these new\nplanets helps in exploring the diverse compositional range of short-period\nplanets, and will aid our understanding of the physical characteristics of both\ngas giants and low-density planets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2016 19:44:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Nov 2016 09:48:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-22"}
