robability of less than 0.005% for\nthis event to be of atmospheric origin. Analyzing the arrival directions of all\nevents with reconstructed muon energies above 200 TeV no correlation with known\n$\\gamma$-ray sources was found. Using the high statistics of atmospheric\nneutrinos we report the currently best constraints on a prompt atmospheric muon\nneutrino flux originating from charmed meson decays which is below $1.06$ in\nunits of the flux normalization of the model in Enberg et al. (2008).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Jul 2016 08:31:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Jan 2017 19:09:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 5 Jan 2017 18:48:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-10"}
